{# #### `project_attributes_restaurant_menu` #}

{{SetCustomerMetadataAttribute(
    idn="project_attributes_restaurant_menu",
    field="multiple_fields",
    value={ "title": "3-07. Restaurant Menu [A]", "description": """This attribute stores the restaurant's menu as plain text, which is then used by the system for
handling orders and recommendations.

To ensure the menu is properly formatted, it is recommended to include:

- Dish name
- Description (ingredients, preparation style, special features)
- Category (e.g., \"appetizers\", \"main courses\", \"desserts\", \"beverages\")
- Price

Example:

```txt
- **Margherita Pizza**
Description: Classic Italian pizza with tomato sauce, fresh mozzarella, and basil.
Category: Main Course.
Price: $12.99.
- **New York Cheesecake**
Description: A creamy, rich cheesecake with a crunchy base.
Category: Desserts.
Price: $7.50.
```

If the menu includes this information, the system can better understand customer requests and find
the right dishes during conversations.""", "group": "3. Knowledge Base", "value_type": "string", "is_hidden": False }
)}}

{# #### `project_attributes_restaurant_regular_events_schedule` #}

{{SetCustomerMetadataAttribute(
    idn="project_attributes_restaurant_regular_events_schedule",
    field="multiple_fields",
    value={ "title": "3-08. Restaurant Regular Events - Schedule [A]", "description": """This attribute stores information about regular events in plain text.

It can be used to specify the schedule of recurring events so that the Agent can inform customers
about them.

What to include in this attribute:

- Event name (e.g., \"Live Music,\")
- Days and times (e.g., \"Every Friday at 7:00 PM\" or \"Every first Sunday of the month\")
- Short description (e.g., \"free participation\")
- Additional conditions (e.g., \"Pre-registration required,\", \"Reservation mandatory\")

Example:

```txt
**Live Music:** Every Friday from 7:00 PM to 10:00 PM. Performances by local jazz musicians. Free entry.
```

If this information is added, the Agent will be able to inform customers about regular events when
they inquire about activities at a specific location.""", "group": "3. Knowledge Base", "value_type": "string", "is_hidden": False }
)}}

{# #### `project_attributes_restaurant_signature_dishes` #}

{{SetCustomerMetadataAttribute(
    idn="project_attributes_restaurant_signature_dishes",
    field="multiple_fields",
    value={ "title": "3-09. Restaurant Signature Dishes [A]", "description": """This attribute contains a list of the restaurant's signature or most popular dishes highlighted for
customers.

This list helps the Agent quickly recommend the restaurant's best and most well-known dishes to
guests. It is important to note that this attribute should not include the entire menu – for that,
use `project_attributes_restaurant_menu`.

What to include in this attribute:

- Dish name (e.g., \"Tomahawk Steak\", \"Truffle Pasta\")
- Short description (e.g., \"A juicy, bone-in steak grilled to perfection\", \"Homemade pasta with a
  white truffle sauce\")
- Dish category (e.g., main course, appetizer, dessert)

Example:

```txt
- **Tom Yum Kung** – Traditional Thai soup with shrimp, coconut milk, and aromatic spices.
- **Pasta Carbonara** – Classic Italian pasta with a sauce made from eggs, Pecorino cheese, and pancetta.
- **New York Cheesecake** – A creamy dessert made with rich cream cheese and a crunchy biscuit base.
```

By including only key dishes in this attribute, the restaurant can highlight its best offerings and
help the Agent provide more accurate recommendations to customers.""", "group": "3. Knowledge Base", "value_type": "string", "is_hidden": False }
)}}

